# Copy to .env and fill in credentials:
#   cp .env.example .env          (macOS/Linux)
#   copy .env.example .env        (Windows)
#
# Start proxy:
#   ./start.sh                    (macOS/Linux)
#   .\start.ps1  or  start.bat    (Windows)
#
# First-time setup:
#   uv venv --python 3.12 .venv && uv pip install --python .venv/bin/python -r requirements.txt   (macOS/Linux)
#   powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File setup.ps1   (Windows)
# All three are required. Refresh when expired (typically every 1–12 hours):
#   aws sso login --profile YOUR_PROFILE
#   eval "$(aws configure export-credentials --profile YOUR_PROFILE --format env)"
#   # paste AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, AWS_SESSION_TOKEN into .env
#   # Windows: .\refresh-aws-env.ps1 YOUR_PROFILE
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=
AWS_REGION_NAME=us-east-1

# --- Option B: Long-lived IAM user keys (access key starts with AKIA) ---
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN is not needed.
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_REGION_NAME=us-east-1

# --- Option C: AWS CLI profile (comment out keys above) ---
# AWS_PROFILE=your-profile
# AWS_REGION_NAME=us-east-1
